-- Barclays tells Diamond to forfeit bonuses: Sky TV
-- 
-- Tue Jul 3, 2012 10:13am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/07/03/us-bonus-idUSBRE8620O820120703

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Barclays Plc will ask ex-Chief Executive Officer Bob Diamond to forfeit up to 20 million pounds ($31.38 million) worth of bonuses, Sky News reported on Tuesday. 
 The bonuses consisted of share options awarded under a management incentive scheme that had not yet vested, Sky News said, citing shareholder sources. ($1 = 0.6374 British pounds) (Reporting by  Douwe Miedema  and  Myles Neligan )